Case 3: Add New Language via Admin Panel
Scenario: You want to add Hindi (hi) language.
Step 1: Add Language in Admin Panel

1. Go to /admin/localization
2. Click Add Language button
3. Fill form:
   - Language Code: hi
   - Language Name: Hindi
   - Native Name: हिन्दी
   - Example Text: नमस्ते
     Step 2: Copy Translations from Default Language
     After adding, you have empty translations. Click Copy from Default to copy all English strings to Hindi.
     Step 3: Translate Using Import (Optional)
     If you have a translated JSON file, import it:
     {
     "common": {
     "save": "सहेजें",
     "delete": "हटाएं",
     "cancel": "रद्द करें"
     },
     "auth": {
     "login": "लॉगिन",
     "logout": "लॉगआउट"
     }
     }
     Important - Platform Tagging During Import:
     When you import JSON, you can specify platform:

- Leave empty → Both platforms ["mobile", "web"]
- Select "Mobile" → Only mobile ["mobile"]
- Select "Web" → Only web ["web"]
  This matters because:
- Mobile-only keys won't show in web app
- Web-only keys won't show in mobile app

